# Citation File Format (CFF) — https://citation-file-format.github.io/
# Cite this project in publications using the metadata below.
cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Australian Political Influence Transparency Project"
abstract: |
  A reproducible, source-backed Australian political influence
  transparency platform. Federal-first; state-and-local
  expansion in progress. Combines deterministic parsing of
  public political-finance disclosures (AEC donations, APH
  Register of Interests, AusTender contract notices) with a
  versioned, hash-cached LLM-assisted extraction layer
  (Anthropic Claude Sonnet 4.6) for industry classification,
  contract topic tagging, and structured disclosure-item
  extraction. Cross-source correlation surfaces — never sum
  across evidence tiers — power public-interest analyses of
  donor-contract overlaps and industry-level influence
  patterns. Inter-rater reliability quantified with Cohen's
  kappa for every LLM stage.
type: software
authors:
